Martin Kingston, Vice President of Business Unity South Africa, speaks to Dan Moyane on the calls for the reintroduction of the Temporary Employer/ Employee Relief Scheme or TERS, to assist businesses and workers affected by the latest adjusted level 4 lockdown regulations. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Business Unity South Africa says unspent government money can be used for lockdown wage relief. It is pushing government to reinstate the Temporary Employer/Employee Relief Scheme following tightened restrictions announced this weekend. READ: Labour dept reveals more than R160m in irregular TERS payments Workers in the restaurant and alcohol sectors have been hit hard with alcohol sales banned for two weeks and restaurants limited to takeaway sales. The Unemployment Insurance Fund says it is checking if there is enough money to reinstate TERS.